Its principal Rivers are the Seine, which receives the
Ionne and the Aube; the Marne; the Aiſne;
and the Veſle.

The moſt conſiderable of its Rivers is the Saone;
the Yonne paſſes by Auxerre;
                  Rivers. the Ain through Breſſe; the
Seine, Armenſon and Arroux, take their Originals from
